betterquesting:10.desc:8:
The star found in the hearts of withers has very similar properties to the other 'mythic' magic I have encountered.
The testificates were willing to share that both the ceratures and the artifacts they produce are of their own making. From this, I can infer that mythic magic can indeed come from mundane sources that are not goddess-type beings.
This likely included some artifact, but it is comforting to know that the inaccessible mythic powers I have encountered aren't as alien as they seemed.
